## Migration Considerations

Switching platforms affects SEO temporarily. Expect:

-   2-4 weeks ranking volatility
-   Temporary traffic dips (10-30%)
-   Recovery within 6-12 weeks with proper migration

**Website migration checklist** essentials:

1.  Crawl existing site and export all URLs
2.  Map old URLs to new URLs (1:1 mapping)
3.  Implement 301 redirects for every URL
4.  Migrate all content including metadata
5.  Preserve internal linking structure
6.  Submit updated sitemap to Search Console
7.  Monitor rankings and traffic daily for 4 weeks

Need help? [SEO migration agencies](/services/seo-consulting/) should provide comprehensive migration planning preventing ranking loss.

## The Real Answer

Platform choice matters less than implementation quality. Poor WordPress SEO underperforms excellent Webflow SEO, and vice versa.

Focus on:

-   Comprehensive content covering your topic space
-   Technical excellence (speed, mobile, crawlability)
-   Strategic internal linking
-   Quality user experience

Both platforms can achieve these fundamentals. Choose based on your technical comfort and business requirements, not SEO capabilities alone.

